@startuml


title LND Studio V7.0 - Global Execution Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant ".agent/workflows/\n(Slash Command)" as Workflow
participant "studio/agents/\n(Persona & Engine)" as Agent
participant "SKILL.md\n(Contract & Injection)" as Skill
participant "knowledge/\n(Domain Context)" as Knowledge
participant "modules/\n(Sub-systems)" as Modules
participant "references/workflow.md\n(Step Logic)" as Steps

== 1. Workflow Trigger (Layer 1) ==
User -> Workflow: Trigger Slash Command (e.g. /gooner-audit)
activate Workflow
Workflow -> Workflow: Parse instruction parameters
Workflow -> Agent: LOAD FULL agent yaml (e.g. gooner-editor)

== 2. Agent Bootstrap (Layer 2) ==
activate Agent
Agent -> Agent: Resolve {project-root} via `BOOTSTRAP.md`
Agent -> Agent: Load Global Rules (`global_rule_hub.md`)
Agent -> Skill: Route to designated SKILL.md via action mapping

== 3. Skill & Auto-Injection (Layer 3) ==
activate Skill
Skill -> Skill: Parse YAML Frontmatter & `dependencies` contract
Skill -> Knowledge: Request Read-Only Context (from `knowledge/`)
activate Knowledge
Knowledge --> Skill: Mount context
deactivate Knowledge

Skill -> Modules: Hook into scoring systems/tools (from `modules/`)
activate Modules
Modules --> Skill: Bind interfaces
deactivate Modules

Skill -> Steps: Invoke core methodology / logic
deactivate Skill

== 4. Step Execution & Quality Gate (Layer 4) ==
activate Steps
Steps -> Steps: Execute Micro-file tasks (1..N)
Steps -> Steps: Enforce Pre-Submission Checklists
Steps -> Agent: Return output blob
deactivate Steps

Agent -> Workflow: Pass Output
deactivate Agent

Workflow -> User: Render Final Artifact
deactivate Workflow

@enduml
